Conflicts: conserver-client
Description: Cloud Foundry UAA
 CloudFoundry User Account and Authentication (UAA) Server.
 The UAA is the identity management service for Cloud Foundry. 
 It's primary role is as an OAuth2 provider, issuing tokens 
 for client applications to use when they act on behalf of 
 Cloud Foundry users. It can also authenticate users with 
 their Cloud Foundry credentials, and can act as an SSO 
 service using those credentials (or others). It has 
 endpoints for managing user accounts and for registering 
 OAuth2 clients, as well as various other management functions.

